{
  "texts": [
    "At the aggregate level, poststratification based on VR files is extremely common at the precinct-level, which can be as small as to encompass just over 400 voters.",
    "The use of VR files to generate public opinion estimates is a crucial part of current political campaign practices in the US.",
    "It is often coupled with ML algorithms to generate individual-level predictions.",
    "These predictions can be aggregated at the level of tiny cells, which even when summarised at the geographic level, can represent enhanced privacy risks.",
    "When it comes to the input (collection and storage of data), a technological solution such as differential privacy can successfully protect voters."
  ]
}